{
  "id": "bundle-tiles",
  "name": "Tiles",
  "category": "Bundles",
  "description": "Recursive Tile grid: every Tile can contain four sub-Tiles via the 2×2 SuperTile pattern. SuperTile (2×2), SuperTile4 (4×4), SuperTile8 (8×8), and SuperTile16 (16×16) stamp progressively larger grids by nesting the same pattern. Cardinal directions propagate from outer Tiles to their boundary sub-Tiles via implications. Fully self-similar — no separate type, just Tile.",
